      "result": "**Not a Node.js project** — this is a **Godot 4.6** game project. No `package.json` exists.\n\nFrom `project.godot`:\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Project name** | Camiel alpha-v0.0.1 |\n| **Main scene** | `scenes/main.tscn` |\n| **Renderer** | Forward Plus |\n| **Viewport** | 1280×720 |\n| **Config version** | 5 |\n\nNo `package.json` to report — scripts, dependencies, and devDependencies are not applicable for Godot projects. The project uses Godot's own build/execution model."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "hash": "c7c3d554effd3b4caf424650ddf5278bbc8da475c5750217e0d2bd97d2ffa2a6",
      "result": "\n\n## docs/ Directory Contents\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/T9/Code/projects/Project-Camiel/docs/`\n\n### Files Found (8 total)\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `README.md` | Entry point with project status at **alpha-v0.0.1** |\n| `project-overview.md` | Goal, target audience (3yo children), controls, GitHub links |\n| `roadmap.md` | Alpha v0.0.1 done + v0.0.2/v0.0.3 ideas + design principles |\n| `development-log.md` | Full history: assets → animations → Godot → controller → export → GitHub |\n| `godot-setup.md` | Engine 4.6.2, project structure, physics params, verification script |\n| `assets-and-animations.md` | Asset locations, animation frame table, jump color fix |\n| `build-and-release.md` | Export templates, preset, build command, GitHub Release setup |\n| `ci-and-community-standards.md` | GitHub Actions CI, CodeQL, quality gate, branch protection rules |\n\n### Key Highlights- **Project:** Child-friendly educational game built in **Godot 4.6.2** (GDScript)\n- **Character:** Camiel — a Bernese Mountain Dog-style character with animations (idle, walk, run, jump, sit, sleep)\n- **Current state:** Playable alpha intro with basic movement, color blocks, and UI feedback\n- **Controls:** Arrow/WASD to move, Shift to run, Space/W to jump, S to sit, X to sleep\n- **Repository:** https://github.com/Euraika-Labs/Project-Camiel (public)\n- **CI:** GitHub Actions with quality gate (`quality_gate.py`) blocking AI-slop patterns\n- **Branch protection:** Enforced on `main` with signed commits, linear history, required PR reviews\n- **Builds:** Not committed to git — published as GitHub Release assets"
    },
    {
      "index": 0,
      "hash": "26eaa11890d85ad9e2c2e90871167cb13cddc6ad6ad074d69cb6672ae7cb0b65",
      "result": "\n\n**Results:**\n\n### Found: 1 of 3 files\n\n| File | Path |\n|------|------|\n| ROADMAP.md | `/Volumes/T9/Code/projects/Project-Camiel/docs/roadmap.md` |\n\n**No TODO.md or CHANGELOG.md found** in the project directory.\n\n---\n\n**Full content of `docs/roadmap.md`:**\n\n```markdown\n# Roadmap\n\n## Alpha v0.0.1 Done\n\n- Godot project created.\n- Camiel character assets generated and imported.\n- Camiel animation resource created.\n- Camiel converted to `CharacterBody2D`.\n- Playable intro scene created.\n- Windows export templates installed.\n- Windows alpha build exported.\n- GitHub repository created.\n- GitHub release created with build assets.\n\n## Suggested Next Alpha Goals\n\nKeep the next steps small and child-friendly.\n\n### Alpha v0.0.2 Ideas\n\n- Add a very simple main menu with one big Start button.\n- Add gentle background music and a few soft sound effects.\n- Add one collectible object, such as a star or biscuit.\n- Add one short spoken or written instruction.\n- Add a finish marker so the child can complete the intro.\n\n### Alpha v0.0.3 Ideas\n\n- Add a first educational micro-task:\n  - touch the red block;\n  - find blue;\n  - count 1, 2, 3 objects.\n- Add parent/teacher notes outside the game.\n- Add accessibility checks for font size and contrast.\n\n## Design Principles\n\n- One idea at a time.\n- Clear colors.\n- Large UI.\n- No time pressure.\n- No punishment-heavy failure state.\n- Keep controls minimal.\n\n## Known Technical Improvements\n\n- Add code signing for Windows.\n- Add a GitHub Actions workflow for automated exports.\n- Reduce duplicate legacy assets if repository size becomes an issue.\n- Add a proper title screen.\n- Add a version label inside the game.\n```"
    },
    {
      "index": 1,
      "hash": "0af465e42c6a817279208d403b3d0555249fe113376339e0e56713c9937261b8",
      "result": "\n\n## Root `.md` Files in `/Volumes/T9/Code/projects/Project-Camiel`\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `README.md` | Project overview — Godot 4 intro game for young children, alpha v0.0.1 |\n| `ALPHA_V0_0_1_NOTES.md` | Alpha scope, included features, controls, missing items |\n| `CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md` | Community guidelines — kind, safe, constructive space |\n| `CONTRIBUTING.md` | Dev setup (Godot 4.6.2), verifier command, asset rules, PR expectations |\n| `SECURITY.md` | Supported versions, private reporting instructions, scope notes |\n| `SUPPORT.md` | Where to start — links to docs, issue tracker, security policy |\n\n**Summary:** Project Camiel is a Godot 4 children's game (alpha v0.0.1). All docs emphasize child-friendliness, simplicity, and low pressure. Development uses Godot 4.6.2 with a headless verifier script. Contributions should discuss child-facing design before adding complex interactions. Build artifacts go in GitHub Releases, not git."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "hash": "24012fe853b44ae37f04e724fe1030d7923c7970ea1688db93ee08cca6beff86",
      "result": "\n\n## `.github/` Directory — Contents Summary\n\n**`.gitlab/` does not exist.** Only `.github/` is present.\n\n---\n\n### Files in `.github/`\n\n| Path | Content |\n|---|---|\n| `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md` | PR checklist with age-appropriate experience guidance, Godot scene testing, doc updates, and no large binary commits |\n| `.github/dependabot.yml` | Weekly GitHub Actions updates on Mondays at 08:00 Brussels time, max 5 open PRs, commits prefixed `ci:` |\n\n---\n\n### `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/`\n\n- **`bug_report.yml`** — Bug report template with fields: summary, steps to reproduce, version, expected behavior. Label: `bug`\n- **`feature_request.yml`** — Feature request template scoped for young children. Fields: idea, child value, scope (Very small → Not sure). Label: `enhancement`\n- **`config.yml`** — Blank issues enabled, links to project docs\n\n---\n\n### `.github/workflows/` (4 workflow files)\n\n| File | Trigger | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| **`ci.yml`** | push/PR to `main`, manual | Runs repository hygiene (quality gate, file size check ≤95MB, conflict markers), verifies Godot project (import, resource check, smoke test), and exports a Windows build artifact |\n| **`codeql.yml`** | push/PR to `main`, weekly cron | Checks if CodeQL is available (public repos or Advanced Security enabled), then analyzes `.github/workflows` for security issues |\n| **`dependency-review.yml`** | PR to `main` | Runs GitHub's dependency review action, fails on high-severity vulnerabilities |\n| **`release.yml`** | git tag (`alpha-v*` / `v*`) or manual dispatch | Resolves tag, builds Windows exe + zip via Godot 4.6.2, uploads to GitHub Release |\n\n---\n\n### `.github/codeql/`\n\n- **`codeql-config.yml`** — Uses `security-and-quality` query suite, scoped to `.github/workflows`\n\n---\n\n**Key observations:**\n- This is a **Godot 4.6.2** game project (`Project-Camiel`) targeting children\n- No `.gitlab/` directory → no GitLab CI configuration\n- CI is GitHub-only, with a full Windows build/export pipeline\n- CodeQL only scans the Actions workflows themselves, not the Godot/GDScript codebase\n- Dependabot only tracks GitHub Actions (not npm/pip/Go deps)"
    }
